{
  "summary": "This paper introduces Text Structure Prediction (TSP), a novel inter-sentence pretraining task designed to enhance large language models by exploiting richer text structure information. Unlike existing inter-sentence tasks (NSP, SOP, SSO) that falter at larger scales, TSP consistently improves performance across Small, Base, and Large model scales on the SuperGLUE benchmark. The method involves classifying sentence pairs based on six hierarchical and ordering relationships, providing more robust self-supervised signals.",
  "strengths": [
    {
      "point": "Addresses Scaling Limitations",
      "evidence": "TSP successfully improves performance at larger model scales where existing inter-sentence tasks either fail to improve or degrade performance."
    },
